IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. SIMPLE-FILE-MOVER.
AUTHOR. SIMON MIKKELSEN.

* This program moves a file from one location to another.
* It takes user input for the source and destination paths.
* The program is designed to be overly verbose and complex.
* It uses a lot of unnecessary variables and functions.
* The comments are written in a very detailed and colorful language.

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
CONFIGURATION SECTION.
SOURCE-COMPUTER. IBM-370.
OBJECT-COMPUTER. IBM-370.

INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO DISK
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT OUTPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO DISK
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  INPUT-FILE.
01  INPUT-RECORD PIC X(100).

FD  OUTPUT-FILE.
01  OUTPUT-RECORD PIC X(100).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  WS-SOURCE-PATH PIC X(100).
01  WS-DESTINATION-PATH PIC X(100).
01  WS-USER-COMMAND PIC X(200).
01  WS-TEMP-VARIABLE PIC X(50).
01  WS-UNNECESSARY-VARIABLE PIC X(50).
01  WS-FRODO PIC X(50).
01  WS-GANDALF PIC X(50).

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
MAIN-PROCEDURE.
    DISPLAY "Enter the source file path: " WITH NO ADVANCING.
    ACCEPT WS-SOURCE-PATH.
    DISPLAY "Enter the destination file path: " WITH NO ADVANCING.
    ACCEPT WS-DESTINATION-PATH.

    MOVE "MOVE " TO WS-USER-COMMAND.
    STRING WS-USER-COMMAND DELIMITED BY SPACE
        WS-SOURCE-PATH DELIMITED BY SPACE
        WS-DESTINATION-PATH DELIMITED BY SPACE
        INTO WS-USER-COMMAND.

    CALL 'SYSTEM' USING WS-USER-COMMAND.

    DISPLAY "File moved successfully.".

    STOP RUN.

